text: I actually think HnC should have used the Joker in the first round. Rather than use it in an uncertain match in a following round, it's better that they use it in the match that's a guaranteed win. You can try to drive up the bet as much as possible to reap the most benefits by making smaller hesitant raises to seem like they are not confident in their card (i.e. not using their Joker) because Woozi seemed like he was prepared to put a lot down. Like if you need to "throw out" a card because you suspect you may tie or even lose, it shouldn't be the powerful Joker card, right? Just throw out one of your other cards and get it to tie, because that is better than losing.

author: @atomicwings1102
text:
I understood it but it might be hard to explain but let me try-
There are three teams. Each team has 400 chips (100 for each member). There are five rounds of the game- in each round 15 cards will be divided randomly among the three teams. Those 15 cards consist of equal number of rock, paper, and scissors cards. Each team also has a joker card (I think? I am not sure if joker card is extra or part of the 15 cards)
Now in each round there are sub-rounds where one member from one team will challenge another team and they go to the dealer and basically bet on whether they will win the rock paper scissors game through the cards they have chosen. Whoever wins gets the chips from the bet. Once they have played a card they can't use it anymore in that round and everyone is informed about which cards were used in each sub-round. So the teams can try to predict which cards the other teams have and strategise according to that. 
If a team loses all their chips they can't play anymore. They can use the joker card only once in the entire game (I think) and they can choose to make the joker card either rock paper or scissors according to their predictions of what the other person has.

Lol I hope it makes sense. The process of getting is not very clear to me though
